Usage
*****

Basic Syntax
============

   kitty-launcher [OPTIONS] [COMMAND]


Options
=======

 -h, --help       Display help message
 -V, --version    Display version information


Commands
========

 <SESSION_NAME>
     Launch a kitty session using the specified session name. The program
     will search for the session configuration file in multiple standard
     locations.

 --create <NAME>
     Create a new session configuration file. Creates a file named
     <NAME>.session in ~/.local/etc/kitty/ using z-tools.session as a
     template (if available).


