File Discovery
**************

Search Paths
============

The program searches for session configuration files in this order:

  1. ./etc/kitty/                  (current directory, highest priority)
  2. ~/.local/etc/kitty/           (user home directory)
  3. /opt/etc/kitty/               (optional system-wide)
  4. ~/.config/kitty/              (kitty standard location, lowest priority)


Extension Auto-appending
=========================

If a session name doesn't end with .session extension, the program will:

  1. First try to find a file with the exact name provided
  2. If not found, retry with .session extension appended

Example: Searching for "dev" will try:
  - dev (exact match)
  - dev.session (with extension)

In all 4 search directories, for a total of 8 attempted paths.


Error Reporting
===============

When a session is not found, the program displays:

  • The session name that was searched for
  • All 8 attempted file paths (in order of search priority)
  • Suggestions on how to create the session file
  • Clear indication of which directories to use


