Creating Sessions
*****************

Using the --create Command
===========================

To create a new session configuration file:

   kitty-launcher --create <SESSION_NAME>

This command will:

  1. Create the ~/.local/etc/kitty/ directory if it doesn't exist
  2. Copy the z-tools.session template (if available)
  3. Create a new file named <SESSION_NAME>.session
  4. Display the path to the created file


Template Files
==============

The --create command uses z-tools.session as a template. To customize:

  1. Edit ~/.local/etc/kitty/z-tools.session
  2. Run kitty-launcher --create with your desired name
  3. The new session will be created from your customized template


Default Template
================

If no z-tools.session template exists, a basic template will be created with:

  • Main tab
  • Development tab
  • Default launch command


Editing Sessions
================

After creating a session file, you can edit it directly:

   $EDITOR ~/.local/etc/kitty/<SESSION_NAME>.session

For session file format documentation, see:
https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/conf/


