Environment Variables
**********************

HOME
====

Used to determine the user's home directory for locating configuration files.

   export HOME=/home/username

If not set, the program will fail to locate user-specific configuration
directories and will not be able to create sessions.


KITTY_CONF_DIR
==============

Set by kitty-launcher before launching kitty to point to the directory
containing the selected session configuration file.

   KITTY_CONF_DIR=/path/to/config/dir kitty --session /path/to/config

This variable tells kitty where to find its configuration files.


