Limitations and Workarounds
****************************

No Absolute Path Support
=========================

The current version does not support specifying absolute paths directly
to prevent security vulnerabilities.

   Workaround: Create symlinks in one of the standard search directories
   pointing to your configuration files.


Limited Template Customization
===============================

The --create command only supports z-tools.session as a template.

   Workaround: Edit ~/.local/etc/kitty/z-tools.session to customize
   the default template, then create new sessions.


Single Template per System
==========================

All new sessions created with --create use the same template.

   Workaround: After creating a session, edit the file directly to
   customize it.


Future Enhancements
===================

Planned features for future versions:

  • Support for multiple templates via --template option
  • Support for absolute paths with --config option
  • Session file deletion with --delete option
  • Session list command with --list option
  • Import/export functionality


